content: I despise BB. It would be convenient if it was more user-friendly. This is an app on my phone, yet it constantly kicks me out so I have to log back in, and it doesn't have an auto-fill option. Sometimes it won't sync properly, so it won't have updated grades that the site does. My lectures are recorded for later use, yet I can't access them on the app at all. I never get notifications for due assignments or anything. Almost a waste of phone storage; 1 extra star for minor convenience of an app.

After I install it, the app will work appropriately for a couple days, but it isn't long until I get an error message on the home feed saying "It looks like there's an error on our side please try again" and it leaves me with an outdated feed, something I simply cannot deal with as I'm a full-time college student. If the app would update appropriately and stay working, I see no reason why it shouldn't be 5 stars. Layout is awesome and user friendly, the app just will not stay updated.

Interface is smooth and clean, and it's easy to understand, but I can't get current grades to load at all sometimes. When I do, it goes right back to old grades next time I log in. it's just perpetually behind, which defeats the purpose. I'm going to try it again this semester. Please fix the loading issues!

At first I was excited to know I didn't have to open up blackboard in desktop mode on my phone and could just use the app, but with the glitching and the inability to ever look at grades it's not even worth it. It is a pretty interface, and if it actually worked it would be great, but overall, it's just more frustrating than it's worth.
New update ruined the perfectly running app. Doesn't sort courses corresponding to current semester, rather have to scroll all the way down to access recent courses.

Both the website and the app are quite confusing to me, however the app ultimately confuses me more. I find myself unable to navigate at times, endlessly scrolling and going back and forth on pages until I stumble upon what I'm looking for. The color palette is also confusing - white background with black text makes things much easier to skim over for me. Overall, I think that there is a lot of room for improvement in this app.
I would have given 3 stars, since the app has always been subpart in usability. Now I have to add HOW EXTREMELY SLOW it has become! Painful to use...

during my previous semester, this app would send multiple notifications for each announcement. During this semester, I have only received notifications for 2 or 3 announcements while there have been upwards of 20 announcements. Very glitchy, please fix these inconsistencies. There are some benefits to this app such as the calendar that tells you when things are due, but notification management should be a high priority for the developers so students know whats happening in their classes.

Well it WAS a great app, until the latest update. I was signed out and now I can't sign back in because the window where it asks you to allow cookies will not scroll down far enough to be able to press the accept button, preventing me from logging in or doing anything else after that. I use this app all the time for school, can this issue please get fixed??

This app isn't terrible. It gets the job done, but the last update is causing for half of my things (including grades) not to show up the right way. When it is properly working, it does what it's intended to do. Just know that you cannot always see some things that are there when you get on a computer. The app isnt capable to show and do everything. After two updates, I am still having issues opening things I used to be able to see or open. I can't even see my grades anymore.

I have been using this app as a supplement to using my computer for online classes. The best use it has is to respond to people's discussion board posts when I am not toting my computer around. That being said, it lacks in a few places. 1. There is no local Host for PDFs. 2. same for PowerPoint. 3. Same for audio. I think that being able to study and work on homework in a handheld format would be a big improvement.

The app looks nice but is buggy and inconsistent. It sends the same notifications multiple times a day. When you click on the notification, it won't take me to the announcement/update/etc it's notifying me about. When I go to check my gradebook, I have to refresh it several times. Usually I have to open and close the app a couple times to get it to work. The app is so inconvenient, it's almost better to go to blackboard using your phone's web browser.

When it actually works, it works great. My biggest problem is that every time I go to see my grades from the app on my phone it says "something went wrong." Had to reinstall on several occasions to get the grade window to load. Also, notifications get through about %50 of the time. If your school uses this, the website is the way to go.

This app works but the functionality is completely subpar. For example if I do daily bonus questions through the app, they don't update and you can't see if you got the question right. On top of that, if you do the question and it shows you got credit in the app, it doesn't send that information to the PC. When I log onto my computer and see if I got the questions complete, it shows I haven't done them.

This app needs some fixes. I think it has the prospects of being a good app, but the way the app handles needs improvement. The format is sub par at best, the tests are either not working or unresponsive. Often times the assignment instructions do not appear. It can be a better app but it needs improvement.

This app used to work okay, but something broke. For the past flew months, the content displays incorrectly. I can see most of the content on a tablet, but on a phone (multiple android devices) I can only see about the left third of a page. Can't resize content, zoom, or scroll left to right. Imagine only being able to see the left column, and the first few words of each sentence. Forget about checking grades. That's basically impossible. You can't scroll down past the first few assignments.

I love the layout. It's easy to navigate and very very helpful for me with online classes. Only problem is the app isnt very reliable as it's been crashing constantly. I couldn't even open it on my phone at all today. I have a new phone with no issues whatsoever. I have a samsung galaxy, maybe it's just not as compatible as opposed to apple. Still disappointing.

Honestly the app has always been a bit gimmicky but now I can't even check my grades on the app "something's wrong" is the error message I get for every single class, mind you it works perfectly fine on desktop. You can't open certain files others you can it depends on what software you have downloaded on your phone and for goodness sake stop making me sign in every single time I get on the app, it's ridiculous

Doesn't work as well as it should. It's for college students so everything should work properly. Certain assignments do not appear. For some assignments, you need another app in order to complete. Also, when responding to class discussions, no word count is displayed which is inconvenient. This app could and should be a lot better. I use my laptop for the most part since the app falls short.

It was fine until recently, now I have to Uninstall and reinstall once or twice a week because it freaks out and enters a perpetual black screen every few days. That and the announcements page doesn't send me to the announcement I want to look at anymore, and will chose an older one for me to read instead. Layout is fine, but isn't convenient for checking assignments anymore.

content: new update changes sucks. You do not stay logged in and get notifications to your phone. I hit the remember me button numerous times but still have to manually put info. Blackboard is great for the most part, but the app is not consistent with loading final grades in real time. In addition, the inability to review to teacher's comments on graded submissions within the app is quite restrictive. Also, the incompatibility with Google Drive documents displays the laziness of Blackboard's development team. Those errors disallow me from rating this app higher. When said errors are fixed, I will update my rating.

Posting about learning what's new about blackboard when I first open the app. No matter how many time I dismiss them they pop right back up and they're over a year old. Opening any notifications leads me to a screen that I can't open anything on because most of the images or text fail to render properly. Also, a majority of the course documents I can open on a PC I cannot find links for in the app. Fun fact: my school is switching away from blackboard and is using canvas next year, so even the school disliked it.

Any number of common blackboard functions just flat don't work. Like "mail," which tries to launch ebook readers instead. Or chat, which seems to come up in offline mode. Recognizing links in discussion group headings is hit or miss. Grade syncing is iffy at best, and YOU CAN'T GET TO THE INSTRUCTOR COMMENTS on your grades. This also means you can't get at writing assignment comments. This is essentially slapped together, and it shows.

It shows what is needed, but being unable to open Word documents is absurd. Also, the fact that there is NO way to turn off or edit notification preferences unless you log into the web version is really tedious. I keep experiencing a bug where "important alerts" from years ago keep showing up no matter if I dismiss them every time I open the app. Please update soon, more students than ever are online this semester, these issues shouldn't be a thing in a modern education app.

When this app was working it was at best a decent app. I actually preferred the older app because I found it to be more dependable and less clunky. This app now isnt working for me at all. It constantly crashes and has become a total waste of space on my phone. I have better luck skipping the app and just going to blackboard in the browser. I wouldnt reccomend this app to fellow students.

"There seems to be an issue on our end, check back again later." This error shows up almost anytime you try to do anything like check your grades, look at due dates, etc. The app has SOME functionality but overall it's unreliable more often than not.

Please revamp the app so work isn't deleted the second you press one button.

I have 2 accounts with 2different institutions and there is no easy way to scroll between the two accounts. I have to log off completely of one to be in the other. This is frustrating

I have been using this app for over a year without issue and loved the convince of taking my school work on the go with me. However the last update a week or so ago did something and now my classes say no longer available or it says my classes have ended. I have no issues logging in on my laptop so it has to be an app issue.

Recently I have to use a web login to get in to the app (which I usually do), however, it don't take you to the app format but the web layout, which is so annoying because it don't work properly. Please sort out this technical issue. I usually enjoy this app.

I love this app. The downside is that no matter what I do I cannot get notifications from this App. I have to check it 3-4x a day to ensure I do not miss important announcements from my courses. Other than that the navigation is great and it is easy to use.

This app it's super nice on my phone I can do everything with it I can find everything super easy but every time I want to come back I have to clear the cache or erase the app and install it again because it doesn't want to work anymore.
Its buggy, especially during submissions. Please fix. Even lecturer stopped believing me. BB should be responsible for having a buggy app instead of my assignment marks.
A good app. Better than using a mobile browser to open Blackboard. Not yet worthy of five stars though. Otherwise, fair experience.
The most important feature of the app which is "notification" is not working at all. I have to open the app on order for it to tell me there is new content!!!!
The mobile app is not pleasant.As it does not display all the things.The emails we send to lectures using the app.Don't go through sometimes.And has other buggy things that i have not mentioned.
The user interface is not intuitive and just feels like a mobile browser for blackboard instead of a mobile port version of the blackboard.
I find it very helpful to me it helps me navigate my courses easily and it's very easy to understand the Blackboard app 👌🏿
Not sure if it is the app or the school, but not every feature functions as expected. Pretty solid app though. Use it 60% of the time I'm schooling.
replyContent: Thank you for the feedback and we apologize for the issue you are experiencing.  Your school/university IT department should be able to help sort out any login issues you are experiencing.  We recommend contacting them to troubleshoot.

content: Honestly I just finished my final exam at 10:24 am. The deadline was May 4th at 11:59 pm and the app only notified me of an announcement that my teacher had posted earlier in the day an hour after the window for my final closed. I'm lucky that I'm very aware of my deadlines but this huge delay in notifications may cost a student their final grade the next time this happens.
It's easy to use but it can sometimes give problems when it comes to connections
Please add dark mode support. I don't understand why we don't have this feature support. It's unacceptable.
Its good but i hope i can choose the speed of the recordings cuz some of my recording are 3 hours long
When it works, it's great. Most of the time I opt for using my pc however.
I use this app because of my tasks but so many glitch like I answer but the teacher can't see it and some task is messing so I can't answer it on time

The mobile app is lacking many features that my college's desktop web portal provides (provided through Onelogin). For example, I can view grades from assignments, but I can't view my professor's written feedback. Attached documents don't always load properly. There is also no dark theme available, which is important as many phones nowadays have OLED displays.

Honestly, the basic idea of the app is great. Ultimately, it comes in handy because as a mother & wife, I have multiple tasks & errands to complete outside of school. It allows me to complete coursework, no matter where or what I'm doing. It's more versatile, travel friendly, & practical compared to a laptop. A couple of things I recommend are making the application more user-friendly & easier to navigate with detailed explanations on titles(play, discuss, learn) vs. going in blindly just to ex

The app does what it's supposed to - I can check classes, assignments due, and grades on it. There's no chance I could ever attempt an assignment thru the app... even a multiple choice quiz. The app is not reliable enough for that. It's also updated biweekly with tiny patches or fixes that have had noticeably zero impact on the UI or overall experience. I don't mind the updates, but then they sometimes take 5 minutes and push an app restart. Overall, an average app. Very average.

the app works fine, but for some reason it won't let me turn in assignments from the app when it once used to. it says that i should use a desktop browser which is strange when i have turned it in through the app with no problem before. sometimes i can't always get to a pc.

Ever since I updated the app, when I boot up the app, it will stay in offline mode and tell me that "content may be out of date" even though I am connected to the internet. I can't figure out what the problem is.

I'm running into an issue logging into the app for the first time. I put in the correct credentials, the login loads for a minute, then doesn't recognize my username or password. I can login perfectly fine on the computer.

Sometimes it doesn't let me see teachers announcements, instead it's just a blank page. When my teachers send me some audio about my work, it just doesn't open. It would be really nice if you guys fix that ^^
The app is fine but it needs alot of improvement or advancement. Like online session on the same app, not on browser... Like give the same access and control as in web version.

The thing is that I am not really used to this learning experience but the Blackboard app is actually a good app for a kick start to online learning, because it is having all the necessary tools and information about it.
Great app, however push notifications aren't coming through and have double checked that all settings are on 'allow'. Constant layout changes are becoming confusing.
For quizzes, there's a glitch wherein answering all items in a multiple type test shows a few items without answers... Occasional logouts, and slow loading time. Other than that, it's great

I'm not sure if this is intended for the new update but blackboard now opens a webpage within the app to get me in blackboard? I don't think I'm actually using the app, just the mobile website. This happens when I have to login through my university portal. Could I ask how the app is supposed to appear?
It's an OK app. Very limiting and feels very old. Its quite slow, crashes. And there's no Calendar widget for example.

Why is this so slow? I have it on my iPhone as well & I thought that maybe it was my iPhone, but having my Note 5G its still very slow. I used to love Blackboard to get some quick schoolwork done when I wasn't around my laptop. I'm not too fond of the newest updates. Its slowed it down so much!
when your reading the announcements it always glitches and you click on one and it opens a different one so you can't read it. needs major updates..
The app takes soooo long to open..it shows a black screen for 3min. WHY is this??. I've a good connection and big storage
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback - we're looking into the issue and we will have an update soon that fixes the problem.

content: This app is good send you notification at the moment your teacher or lecturer as soon as they make an announcement
Can be problematic when transfering data from one file onto blackboard; alters data appearance but otherwise functional.
Can not open all assignments on the app that is available for the courses.
Could be a lot better and I definitely preferred Canvas for quite a while but it's okay.
Its okay but i wish i could do more assignments with it on my phone.
The app takes longer to update new content, it doesn't update right away.
I would rate 1 star more if sharing screen for mobile phone option would be there.
Not exactly trustworthy to get what you need for your classes. Announcements do not update consistently. This app could be better.
When I try to open a collaborate link, it says it can't connect other than that it's works ok
I like that I can see my grades, I just wish it did more.
They make some problem's in questions, quiz and mcqs.
The latest updates broke the app. What the heck! Viewing my courses crash the app constantly. Help!
The app works fine. I want to know if there is access to past online lectures on the app?
Crashes a lot recently but is great when it works

I can view all my grades and classes, but I can't turn in any assignments. Considering my class is a learn-at-your-own-pace, the big red grade isn't helping me much. Besides that though its okay... Does its job.
I don't like how BB now logs me out and I have to keep logging in.
Unreliable....and dangerous in that way. Nice when working, yet needs work itself
The app is excellent and the response rate is good.
Since updating it, I cant open certain courses. Everytime I try, the app crashes
Updates later and slower than the BB webpage
I can't access my course at Uni of Newcastle after signing in. I click on the course but nothing happens.
Works fast and Sends notifications faster
Freezes difficult to manage multiple classes

It works... for the most part. But opening anouncements(I use the app mainly for announcements) from the home screen(even though the heading text shows new updates) sends me to old announcements which requires me to pick my class first and have to look at announcements from there. Grades could be organized a lot better like they did in the browser.

Update: uninstalled and reinstalled the app and it went back to the mobile format still three stars cause the basic interface only kind of works too but is much better than the weird mobile webpage we were getting directed to. ***Recent update is trash. Instead of showing the easy to use app layout it just feeds you the website version which doesn't work on mobile for anything. What's the point of a mobile app that's just a web container?
replyContent: Thank you for the feedback and we apologize for the issue you are experiencing. Would you mind letting us know what institution/school you attend? That will help us work out the issue. Thanks!

content: As a college student during the pandemic, I rely on blackboard for all of my classes. Some of the assignments are not formated to work with mobile phones, and I have to wait until I am around a pc to submit assignments. Also, I think it would be helpful to a lot of students if blackboard added a calendar feature, which could automatically update with new assignments and due dates, that way we can easily see all upcoming assignments in one place, without sorting through multiple files per class.
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback! The due dates feature in the app should help - https://help.blackboard.com/Blackboard_App/Due_Dates#due-dates-for-all-courses_OTP-0. We have some updates coming soon that will also improve it!

content: Not very user friendly. Not very intuitive

I am a student at UHD and has enjoyed the application before the new update. I was able to get notifications and reminders and now nothing. I have to sign in through the web just in order to see my blackboard. Totally defeats the purpose of being notified of current updates
Useful app, however recently the app keeps sending the same notifications over and over again. This is really annoying and I'm hoping there's a fix for this bug soon.

I like how you can post responses to the discussions and that it will open up the optional reading app (bookshelf) when you click on one of the reading articles. I would like to see the message tab added in the future so I can communicate with the instructor and my team members for group assignments. I would also like to see the instructors feedback on the grading as some can only be viewed when you log on from a desktop.

Missing grades from past courses, would benefit from a widget. I use this on my Android phone because it's the only one available for students. All of its basic functions work fine, but there is clearly room for improvement. Most importantly, I can't view grades from a course I just completed. This should be basic: there's a header under courses that says Current, but Past is missing. Also, why not include a few widgets? Just a quick view of current courses or assignments would help a ton.

The app does not have full functionality, like the website does. I use it to access announcements, grades, and files for my courses. It takes quite a while to update once I open the app. There also appears to be a lag between when my professors add something and when I receive notifications. I did not appreciate having a dozen or more alerts go off at 3:45 am when the professor had added the content the previous day :(

I do appreciate the updated ease of use for the app, however I am disappointed that the functionality to have multiple schools has been lost. I am a student currently enrolled in two programs at two different schools. I used to be able to select my school from the main menu, but now I need to completely log out of my primary program to even check my grades for my secondary program.
The app is great. But im no longer recceiving notification.

I have had only 2 problems with the android app so far. The first, is you can't check messages you receive. If the instructor sends a message to the whole class (not an announcement), you have to access a desktop or laptop in order to see messages in blackboard. Second, there was a survey asking what page we wanted to load by default. I, and the majority, voted for the course page. My app loaded there after that maybe once or twice, and now it's back to loading on the activity stream. Hate it.

I mean, I'll use it, because it's easier than pulling out my laptop. However, it doesn't display images, links to documents often don't work or don't show up, and links to reading and assignments often appear in tiny text that's hard to read and i have better than 20/20 vision. Like much of Blackboard, it's functional, but just barely enough to avoid outright protest. I give it three stars.

It is a great way of communicating with the students, but it makes me nervous getting all these announcements twice through email and the app and then also reading some of them which doesn't apply to me. I realise it is a fast and easy way to communicate with the students, but every time I see an announcement I assume it's about work etc, and then sometimes it's just about someone a lecturer is is looking for, but it is a great way of knowing what's going on in every subject. Thanks!

There isn't any info about your class schedule or what room and building they're in unlike the website version of this app. That would be very convenient and I don't see why that isn't in this app. Furthermore, it should give you the option on when to notify you when classes are coming up, for example; reminder set for 11pm and an hour before class starts.

I feel that the app is something most students cannot afford to live without. It is extremely helpful because it notifies you when your teachers make new announcements. It provides access to the grades and online content for courses, which allows students more opportunities to work on assignments when their computer is not readily available. Issues: On the downside many notifications reappear 2-3 times which can become agitating when there are already a lot of notifications to begin with.

Functional, but temperamental. I can check my grades but it'll error out about 10% of the time. Notifications just don't work, period. I can check my course content and discussion boards typically without issue. Overall it functions like a lesser copy of some of the features of the website app. However as a phone app, the features I would expect to use this for (real-time push notifications) don't work and don't provide any options. Disappointing.

Used to work a lot better. I could take quizzes and tests on here before. Now I can't. And the app also logs me off every other time I go to use it. So that's fun. Update: it sseems to be working better now. I haven't used it many times, but so far it hasn't logged me out and is back to how it normally looked. I appreciate you guys responding and changing it. I will continue to use the app and will update my review again if it keeps working well :) thank you
replyContent: Thank you for the feedback and we apologize for the login issue you are experiencing.  We have an update in the works to fix the issue.  Look for an app update soon.

content: It's easier than logging in all the time to the website, and I like it better now that I'm more familiar with it. I like the automatic notices. Transitioning from items and classes is difficult at times because of their location on the app, but all in all I use it daily and like it. Oh only other issue is writing on app from phone is very difficult.
Takes forever to sync updates. App works good and is a life saver at times, but i get so confused when it tells me i have assignments that i did and turned in but yet at 39 days late

This app is pretty average it has just what you need when you can't get to your computer, but the interface lags. My experience with the application is two semesters into the school year. What I have noticed was that I get pop-up notifications but it wouldn't load in the app. Another instance was reviewing assignments in the app, but it not reflect on the website. The lag in user interface is a minor inconvenience. Compared to Canvas, I'm not impressed with its performance but I still use it.

I really appreciate this app for telling me when I have announcements or grade updates; however, the app will continue to notify my multiple times a day for many days after the posting has been viewed and there isn't any way to make changes in the settings. This is particularly aggravating when I have a poor grade posted and the constant reminder on push notification really puts me into a deeper funk. I deleted the app the first time I got it because of this but I am unfortunately dependent on it

So far I have trouble following up the app. I previously used Canvas and I really enjoyed it. Now I am let wondering because the menus are not very helpful, I don't have a to do list that tracks the assignments for the day as well as mark the ones that are already completed. Instead I have all assignments and announcements for the semester cluster where you have to read what is what and waste some more time wondering. I really miss Canvas

App takes a while to update and does not always update. I find myself having to log into my school account to confirm my grade after using this app to actually find my grades. This app also sends me multiple notifications for the same update, hours, sometimes days after the announcement/update has been made. I would give this app 2.5 starts out of 3.

I really liked the app before an update was done. Now it logs me out periodically, or if I download a document and try to go back to where I left off (not even 1 minute later), I have to log back in and start all over! Logging back in wouldn't be that big of a deal if it would take me to where I left off! It defeats the purpose of having an app on my phone, if I have to log in 10 times while I'm using it to do an assignment!

Blackboard is a requirement for my college as we use it on a daily. I really with the notification feature worked better and that we could personalize it to notify us as soon as a teacher posts an announcement. Sometimes they dont click the option to have it emailed to us when they post and we dont know its been posted until the next time we login. Meaning they could post a last minute assignment and we may not find out till the next after its due. Also, some of the remind features dont work.

It's ok. You can view your Blackboard shell and the content. My issue is the grade section doesn't sync in real time. You can have a grade post and it won't show up in this app even when you refresh it. Sadly it's the only that I've found that works with my school. I miss the blackboard learn app. This one doesn't compare

Utterly useless! This app worked great for my first semester. They did some kind of update on the break and now I can't log in. I can log into blackboard on the web browser, but the app tells me I have the incorrect credentials. I contacted the company and no response. Don't bother downloading the app, its a complete waste.

This app used to work great, but now it does not work very well at all. I have to sign in like 3 times before I can even get in the actually app. Everytime I open the app, I have to sign in which is really annoying and time-consuming. Also, once I'm in the app, the files never load! I've tried doing this on different wifi connections and still get the same result. I even tried it with my hotspot, but the app still doesn't work well.

This app was working perfect when I first installed it a couple months ago but now with the updates and all it's not working very well the announcements aren't working they're not loading they just keep spinning and spinning and then I get an error message that says oh the problem is ours not yours can we please get this fixed???? other than that I love this app it really helps me with school on the while I'm on the go I get to keep track of what I need to you know work on.
Your app is too slow ,I have been trying to download it for almost 30 mins with no luck ,it cancel .It is not about space or data it's just slow

As of the November 16th update, Apple devices (tested on an iPhone and iPad) seem to be stuck on the "Web login" version of Blackboard instead of going into app view after logging in (like it does on Android devices). I hope this is planned to be fixed soon. Generally I prefer using Blackboard on a computer, but the app is fine if you want quick notifications of announcements and grades on the go.

The app is fine but can do with much improvement. Such as being able to write a test on mobile device. Also When writing a test on the app it does not allow one to write in paragraphs or bullet points. It says it's "free" as long your balance is positive, that's not true! Nevertheless though, it comes in handy

Its a good app, but there are come characteristics on the website that you can't see on the app. For example, in course materials of a course, professors sometimes put a description telling students what to have prepared for the week, but you can't view it on the app.

Nice tool to keep up with your duties and to be updated in case of announcements. I would like to see the due dates/ calendar to be clearer. I can see only the week, and tasks of a selected day. it is necessary to scroll through the weeks to have an idea of your timmings or amount of tasks that are yet to come. I would also like to see a way to link this calendar with my Google phone calendar. Is there a way to do it? Last point, we should be able to open hyperlinks.

Only thing is it won't allow you to see all assignment graded and not yet graded. Other than that I'm ok. update: we use outside links to do homework and test. the professors put the link up but once you are in the app link does not work. it's annoying as I mostly depending on the app to get home work done. also recently I realise I can no long print from the app like I did before

I love using this app for writing discussions or responses. I would give it 5 stars if it was working correctly again. Halfway through this term, I could not access my grades nor graded assignments. Last term I could. Now I get a blank screen-on the bottom it says "Oops somethings not right". I would hope this gets fixed.

The app is pretty helpful except that ALL my courses from my first year at the university up to present are ALL included to my "current" courses. It's annoying and I find it hard to find my "currently enrolled courses" because all of my previous courses are still on thr list. I can't get rid of them, there's no options on your settings. Please fix this.

the app is overall quite functional, however, I do not get notifications at all when content is updated. receiving notifications when content was upload was my entire reason for getting the app. I've tried to update my notification settings and go through app settings. nothing has changed. in terms of viewing PDF and PowerPoint attachments, it works really well and I can follow along in class from my phone.

Could be way better. The app doesn't properly notify you when assignments are upcoming or due half the time, sometimes I will just get a mass of notifications at once. The pages lag far behind the desktop version, giving me errors when trying to view new classes that should have been posted already, and are visible on desktop. UI really needs improvement. It's better than nothing to look up assignments, but I would never primarily rely on this or submit an assignment through it.

The app worked great and was very useful until it updated (the update that changed the menu icon from the chalkboard look to the blue one). Now my grades are not updated timely--it seems to happen randomly, every couple of weeks or so. Also, I can't read the descriptions for any of the assignments nor write my submission from the assignment page. Essentially I can only use Blackboard online now, and the formatting is not nearly as mobile-friendly as the app was. Reinstalling didn't help.

Works great, convenient for doing work on the go. *Edit- For the past week or so I can't check my grades using the app. I have to use my browser. It's just pop up a red bar with an exclamation mark that says "Something's not right." Still doing it after a recent update.

I constantly get a Sign On error. I tried to reinstall the app, clear cache but I get the same error. It used to work but now there is no point in having the app anymore since I have to use a browser to log in. I would give it more than a star for the way it used to work but in the current state I can't use it at all.

The app works fine, but Blackboard doesn't seem to have the infrastructure in place to support the bandwidth necessary due to so many institutions going virtual thanks to the pandemic. Professors are constantly losing connection on Collaborate and lag is so frequent that it's nearly impossible to follow along with whatever the instructor is trying to teach. A version for PC would be very useful, not all phones have the power to support a two-hour live chat.

The app has been "broken" on my Galaxy S8+ since last update. For one, my grades are now highlighted in black, rather than green, red, yellow, etc and won't let me see comments. Also, I have noticed that changes such as assignments being added, must be updated on BB web before they are updated on the mobile app, which takes away the purpose of the app. I also get signed out much more often now. The apps works... to a degree. But it does not have all working features that the web version has.

Pixel 3 - Was excited at first. Some aspects are very good. However, when accessing sections in my study week the side menu blocks half the screen and the reading pane is squished to three or four characters. Portrait only as well. I tried rotate but didn't work. So much for studying on the bus. 3 stars because I can see my assessment due dates easily.

I really like this. It's very easy thru this app to join my college classes online and get involve in discussion and lots of other things. One thing I didn't like is that not all features are supported in this app version. That's the reason I gave 3 stars. The rest is fine. When I don't log out, I don't even get to log in all the time which is good.

It is good but. I have one query not sure if BB can solve. I have issues with my blackboard where my teacher sometimes, upload stuff on the day, but the students cannot view. Then when it pops up, its a few days alr. And i am sad because, like this, i always feeling that is it me who did not do my due diligence to check blackboard? Or what happened? I feel cheated.

I don't mind the platform, just the app. About there times a semester I have to uninstall and reinstall it to be able to see grades, course content, discussion board, etc. It loads my classes but that's it. it'll be fine for a little while after I reinstall it but it's still getting pretty annoying

Fantastic app, really helps me keep up with my studies on the go. Only reason it didn't get 5 stars is because after the update it keeps logging me out any time I look at anything else on my phone, or even if my screen shuts off after a short period of inactivity. Really annoying to keep having to start over again.
Cant see messages when profesorrs send them

I'd love to get notifications for when assignments are due. Being able to set a thing that reminds me a day before, then 5 hours before, then 1 hour before, and that sort of stuff. Would really make me give this app 5 stars but for now it's 3 b/c it lacks that feature.

Blackboard, but for your phone!. Its getting better than it was when I started using it a year ago. I really only use it to check grades now . I have tried to use it in class discussions, but have encountered issues such as duplicating posts, or not showing posts from classmates. There is an announcement system, but it is always behind or only populates when due dates have passed. It makes for a helpful tool, but do not try to rely on it.

Although functional; "Blackboard offers a modern and delightful mobile learning experience." <----- That statement is a wild exaggeration. It feels like the least amount of time and effort was put into making a workable app for students. I guess, that is the way businesses work with regards to students anyway.

Better. Wish it had better notification settings (and maybe personalization settings?) and was easier to log into when your school has special security settings, but a lot better than before, easier to navigate. My only true complaint is that it still doesn't show everything from the courses, like sometimes all announcements don't show or assignments aren't listed or can't be opened from the app.

The app crash when trying to add a document or picture and when pressing the back botton It logs me out as well. Sometimes when entering both correct username and password it shows that the app accept it and in a second takes me back to re enter the password and username, just make the app better by allowing the option to enable or disable the " stay loged in " or remember this account option plus in the courses discussion or the app in general to auto save everything as a draft.

it's a good app, on the famous 1 to 10 scale, I would give this app a 5 or 6 more a 5. We do NOT have access to over 50% of the course material. I can NOT access assignments or lectures which leaves, a reminder app with a few abilities, like grades, etc. not a lot of use in college!

The app is useful in that I like getting push notifications for new announcements, but the amount of stuff you simply can't do from the app is a serious drawback (to the experience of Blackboard itself, which already is not stellar). Your course splits you into groups? Well, go to the website to view that. Trying to use this app for anything beyond the push notifications is a constant fight to not have to move to my pc instead.

It works okay if you want to access your course material on your phone. But there is no dedicated emailing option, I have to load the desktop version through the app. Also your session times out constantly so you have to log in multiple times a day, really annoying and unecessary.

The app is very good BUT I have a problem on the marks section. I HAVE SENT AN EMAIL THROUGH THE APP, BUT I HAVE NOT BEEN ANSWERED YET! When I enter this section, it is written that "something went wrong" !!! It is a really big problem for me. I kindly request you to help me as soon as possible!

So far I like the app, however, it can cause a little bit of panic with grades as they update a little funny. Also, the options to pull up class convos is limited. I do like being able to read my assignments and see what's up next.

Its frustrating and annoying to use, the blackboard collaborate does not work in the app for me and I have to access it through the website. Sometimes I can't submit my assignments for some reason and I don't know that until the teacher contacts me. It took me a whole month to figure out how to change my profile picture, turns out it was because I didnt toggle my display option, which is only on the website and not the app itself. This doenst work very well as an app.

Oh God why. UI is gross looking and slow. I have to click on a class, back out, and then click on the class again to check if my grade updated. I have re login almost constantly. There's gotta be a better system out there, but I'm stuck with blackboard because my uni requires it.

It would be 5 stars but now it just keeps forcing me to sign in but doesn't actually sign me in. I've been stuck on the login page for 2 days now. i like the ease of the app, but don't like how some of the content isn't displayed, such as instructions under an assignment. Would really appreciate if you fix my login issue.

There should be a better way to organize your classes. I have classes from my last, last semester still available in the courses. I have to scroll through all of the classes to go to the one I want. It would be more convenient if there were folder options to be able to categorize your classes by semester, making it easier to access. Please consider this option. Thank you. Keep working.

Certainly the worst mobile lms app I've experienced. Most functions are usable but the whole experience is clumsy and errors are common. Cumulative grades take a while to update even if I can see the graded assignment on blackboard, many files won't open (or download) through the app, submission through the app is also a game of chance as it often won't work. Also it often defaults to mirror the website when opening certain folders... so why not just use the website?
replyContent: We’re sorry you are experiencing an issue with the app.  Would you mind providing more information on the issue you are experiencing in order for us to help and resolve?  Thanks!

content: Its functionality is limited so I'm not quite sure what the point of this app even is. Commonly can't display course contents except pure text, and even then the formatting gets weird. Can still check due dates and announcements though, this format's a little easier to glance at that then in "desktop mode" on a phone browser.

This Blackboard is Quite helpful, Titles and Subheadings are easily located. Though I find it very annoying that I have to keep logging in quite frequently after being inactive for a moment. replyContent:
Hi Raghavi, I am sorry that you faced this issue. Sometimes the cached data in the Android App will lead to your device go out of sync. Please try out the below steps:
Go to Settings.
Tap on Apps 
Find the app that keeps crashing & tap on it.
Next, tap clear cache
Tap Force stop.
Go back to the Home screen & launch the app again.

Hope this helps.
